cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.CR 

This paper deals with the Medium Access Control (MAC) protocol for radio distributed networks, which is a subfield of computer networking. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses channel capacity improvement and fairness considerations, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM), respectively. The paper presents experimental results, which suggest that it may also belong to the systems and control (cs.SY) category. Finally, the paper discusses collision reduction, which is related to cryptography and security (cs.CR).
